IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE LAB — LAYER 4 COMPLETE
Wings Global Trade · Product Page
Mode: SPATIAL-DESIGN (NOT BUILD-3D)
Spatial archetype: The Machine — "function made beautiful," the inside of a precision instrument.

================================================================
PERFORMANCE CONTRACT
================================================================
- Zero Three.js. Zero WebGL. Zero canvas. Zero 3D.
- All presence is CSS + inline SVG (static, no animation loops).
- EnvironmentalContextLayer renders ONE tiled SVG <pattern> — GPU-cheap, no JS.
- No requestAnimationFrame loops introduced by Layer 4.
- Safe for LATAM mobile (the constraint that ruled out 3D in the shipping report).
- Inspection Mode + FieldReport use AnimatePresence height transitions only —
  no layout thrash, GPU-composited opacity/height.

================================================================
SPATIAL EXPERIENCE SUMMARY — what makes the buyer feel "inside the machine"
================================================================

1. EnvironmentalContextLayer.tsx  [REWRITTEN]
   The machine's world, rendered as the document it would live inside, held at 3% opacity.
   - maquinaria-agricola → nested TOPOGRAPHIC CONTOUR lines (a terrain survey, with a
     spot-height tick), not a single sinewave. Reads as a topo map.
   - camiones / buses → orthogonal WAREHOUSE FLOOR PLAN: bay grid, dimension ticks,
     loading-dock hatching. Reads as logistics floor plan, not a generic grid.
   - equipo-industrial → engineering REGISTRATION GRID with corner crosses.
   - Removed dangerouslySetInnerHTML (XSS-shaped pattern) → real React SVG.
   - Removed 100vw/100vh fixed sizing that caused horizontal scroll → inset-0 + overflow-hidden,
     opacity moved to the wrapper (Tailwind), preserveAspectRatio="...slice" for full bleed.

2. TechnicalSilhouette.tsx  [REWRITTEN]
   Real engineering side-elevations, not placeholder shapes. 1.5px warm-white monoline on
   navy, resting on a gold 0.5px datum rule with end-ticks (the silhouette has a baseline to
   sit on — dimensional presence without 3D weight).
   - Tractor: large rear drive wheel (r=40) + hub rings, small front wheel (r=20),
     trapezoid body, CAB OUTLINE (was missing), roof overhang, exhaust stack, grille ticks.
   - Truck: cab + window, cargo box with door seam, chassis baseline, two wheels.
   - Bus: long rounded body, windscreen rake, 4 windows, door with seam, two wheels.
   - Forklift: chassis, operator overhead guard, MAST with two diagonal cross-braces,
     carriage, two forks extending left, two rear wheels (was the weakest — now correct).
   - Label set to sentence case to match brand register.

3. JumpNavigation.tsx  [REWRITTEN — reframed from nav bar to document index]
   The serious buyer controls the depth; the platform does not control the flow.
   - Added a document POSITION REGISTER on the left edge: "02 / 04" (tabular DM Mono),
     so the buyer reads where they are in the document.
   - Four words (Variantes · Especificaciones · Usos · Consultar), gold underline on active,
     aria-current on the active section. Sticky, appears after 200px scroll.

4. FieldReport.tsx  [CONTENT KEPT — threshold refined]
   Content was already operationally real (altitude 3,200 msnm / carburetor verification,
   SUTRAN, MTC, INDECOPI, ZOFRATACNA/ZOFRI admission). Kept verbatim.
   - Threshold refined: added "REG · OPS" document-reference tag beside the header, so opening
     it reads as breaking the seal on a technical field document, not expanding a marketing FAQ.

5. ProductSpecTable.tsx  [INSPECTION MODE ADDED — game-designer's hover tooltip PRESERVED]
   Two distinct depths of curiosity, intact and non-overlapping:
   - game-designer's 1.5s HOVER tooltip (passive reward for lingering) — untouched.
   - NEW click-driven INSPECTION MODE (deliberate deep investigation):
     * clickedSpec state; spec value becomes a button (.spec-value-inspectable).
     * Inline AnimatePresence panel: spec name in DM Mono 10px uppercase gold,
       extended explanation in Flexo 13px navy, "Rango de mercado" line when available.
     * Dismiss on Escape or outside click. Grid card spans full width while open.
     * specInspectionFor() reuses game-designer's keyword identity map, extended content.

6. globals.css  [Inspection Mode styles appended]
   .spec-value-inspectable (cursor + gold hover at 150ms) under @layer utilities.

================================================================
QUALITY BAR — the test applied to every element
================================================================
"Does the user feel they are inside a precision instrument, or browsing a catalog?"
- Topo/floor-plan ambient ground → the machine has a WORLD, not a CSS trick.
- True silhouettes on a datum rule → the product has DIMENSION, legibly drawn.
- Document register + jump index → the buyer NAVIGATES a document, controlling depth.
- Field report as a sealed ops document → presence of FIELD EXPERIENCE, not a brief.
- Inspection Mode → the page becomes a LEARNING SURFACE on intentional click.
Silence held: nothing added that does not add presence. 3% opacity, monoline, no decoration.

TypeScript: all 5 Layer 4 files typecheck clean (verified). The only project tsc errors
are in InquiryForm.tsx (experience agent's pulseGold prop, task #16) — outside my ownership.
